{"updated_at": {"date": {"d": "24", "m": "06", "Y": "2026"}, "time": {"H": "21", "M": "15", "S": "02"}}, "news": [{"title": "ORA Group forays into integrated township and plotted development through ORA Land; Unveils vision for landmark community at Karjat", "para": "ORA Group is expanding into integrated townships and plotted developments with ORA Land, launching its first project, 'BluBay,' in Karjat. This move aims to redefine land ownership with modern infrastructure and lifestyle amenities. Indian cricketer Suryakumar Yadav has been appointed as the brand ambassador for BluBay, highlighting a vision for balanced and meaningful living. The development capitalizes on Karjat's growing appeal as a real estate destination.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/brand-connect-initiative/ora-group-launches-blubay-a-new-era-in-integrated-township-development-in-karjat/131972196?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-104469/131972196.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "brand-connect-initiative"}, {"title": "Indore civic body issues notices to 47 over building permit fraud", "para": "Indore Municipal Corporation has issued notices to 47 property owners and consultants for manipulating building permissions to avoid fees and reduce taxes.  Scrutiny of online approvals revealed applicants exploited the automated system, falsely claiming vacant land, amalgamating plots, and under-reporting construction areas. This allowed them to pay significantly less than mandated fees. The civic body is now reviewing past permits to recover dues and penalize offenders.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/regulatory/indore-municipal-corporation-cracks-down-on-building-permit-fraud/131972331?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-669846/131972331.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "regulatory"}, {"title": "Official suspended over illegal A-khatas to 50 properties in Bengaluru", "para": "Bengaluru West City Corporation has suspended assistant revenue officer K.S. Manjula for allegedly issuing A-khatas to over 50 properties in an unauthorized layout. The land, located in Herohalli village, was under litigation with a court order to maintain status quo. Officials cite serious tampering with records and violation of service rules, initiating a departmental inquiry.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/regulatory/bengaluru-officer-suspended-for-issuing-illegal-a-khatas-to-over-50-properties/131972309?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-368684/131972309.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "regulatory"}]}